{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines Assignor's representations and warranties regarding the transferred contract, including its enforceability, completeness, lack of disputes, and no default events. It also confirms Buyer's consent to the assignment.",
  "operative_text": "The Assignor represents and warrants that: a. The Transferred Contract is in full force and effect and is enforceable in accordance with its terms; [***] Confidential treatment has been requested for the bracketed portions. The confidential redacted portion has been omitted and filed separately with the Securities and Exchange Commission. b. Exhibit A contains the entire agreement of the Assignor and Buyer relating to the Transferred Contract, and the Transferred Contract has not been amended or modified in any way; c. There are no disputes, pending or threatened, related to the Transferred Contract; d. No event or condition has occurred that is, or with the passage of time would be, a default under the Transferred Contract; and e. Buyer has consented in writing to this Assignment, either in the express terms of the Transferred Contract or in a separate signed consent the Assignor has delivered to the Assignee.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "Joint and several liability is not explicitly addressed, which could create significant risk for the Client if the Assignor defaults on obligations under the contract.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Assignor"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity regarding the mechanics of capital calls and how they will be handled in case of a default or breach by the Assignor.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Capital call mechanics"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause does not specify the governing law for this agreement, which could lead to legal disputes and uncertainty regarding jurisdiction.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Governing law"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause mentions penalty / liquidated damages but doesn't provide specific details on their amount or how they will be calculated. This lack of clarity could lead to disputes and uncertainty regarding the consequences of a breach.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Penalty / liquidated damages"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause mentions indemnification carve-outs but doesn't specify which parties are covered or what specific events trigger these carve-outs. This lack of clarity could lead to disputes and uncertainty regarding the scope of indemnification.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Indemnification"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
